File: A number of reports have surfaced in recent days of senior officials misappropriating COVID-19 funds. JOHANNESBURG - SACP General Secretary Blade Nzimande says the government needs to do more to fight corruption. He says the law should deal with those caught in any corrupt business dealings. READ: ANC meets Cosatu and SACP over public wage bill A number of reports have surfaced in recent days of senior officials misappropriating COVID-19 funds. "We must intensify the struggle to end the tenderisation of the state and the corruption that it breeds and tackle its associated tendencies," said Nzimande. Nzimande was speaking at a briefing to mark the communist party's 99th anniversary.